org.orgName: United States District Court For The Western District of Washington Northern Division

div1.p: In the District Court of the United States for the Western District of Washington. Northern Division.
In the Matter of the Application of Chas. Jackson, for a Writ of Habeas Corpus.
div1.ab: Filed in the United States District Court Western District of Washington Northern Division

F. M. Harshberger, Clerk
By S. E. Leitch, Deputy
div1.p: United States District Court Western District of Washington Northern Division
In the Matter of the Application of CHAS. JACKSON for a Writ of Habeas Corpus.

The above named applicant and petitioner, by his attorneys, having stipulated herein with the respondent through his attorney, for the withdrawal of certain exhibits from the files herein, it is therefore, by the Court hereby considered and ordered, That the respondent Henry M. White, Commissioner of Immigration at Seattle, Washington, be, and he hereby is, permitted and authorized to withdraw from the files and records herein that certain exhibit attached to the return of said respondent herein, said exhibit being a transcript of record of the proceedings and testimony adduced in said proceedings before the Immigration officers of the United States with relation to the deportation of the above named petitioner, and the clerk of the court is hereby ordered and directed to deliever and surrender said exhibit to the said Henry M. White, or his attorney.
Done in open court this 24 day of January, 1919.

closer.signed:
Jeremiah Neterer
United States District Judge
Ralph S. Pierce
Per N.
closer.note: Received Exhibits Charlotte Koenig for Henry M. White Jan 24, '19
